<br>
Sure, you can change some people. Look at Cogito’s story about heights. He got over it, became comfortable, but his friend, who continually went up there, never did.<br>
<br>
You get people who are scared of spiders, and throw them in a room of spiders, some will eventually get used to it, some will not. Same with snakes.<br>
<br>
I suppose I could get tolerant of sweet potatoes if my life depended on eating them, even though now, the very smell of them sends me running into the bathroom.<br>
<br>
If I was kicked in the head once a day, first thing in the morning, I would doubt I would ever get used to it. More than likely I would develop severe insomnia and shit my pants a lot.<br>
<br>
But Elche is right, those are not phobias. I can’t even believe I am throwing out analogies. I am usually not one to do it. And yeah, you couldn’t make me “play” with cotton balls without me putting up a pretty big fight. <p><BR>
